Cut the Rope: Experiments is truly the best physics-based app currently available on the play store. Its high level of polish, interesting puzzles, and amazing physics make for a delectable game that anyone can and should experience. Ironically, I have enjoyed playing Cut the Rope: Experiments much more than its predecessor for the reason that it de-emphasises the use of ropes in favour of mechanical devices that work really well. Most levels do not even have ropes, making for a much satisfying experience. I really do wish that more developers took a cue from ZeptoLab instead of releasing buggy, unpolished apps. This, ladies and gentleman, is how you make a game worthy of the Play Store.

Short version: Texturing issues, music not as good as iPhone, runs poorly on adequate but older hardware, video did not play. YMMV on older phones.  I love cut the rope, I play it on my fiancee's iPhone all the time so I thought I'd buy it. I was rather disappointed when I noticed all of the little glitches because it's been shoe-horned into the Android environment -- it's a cheap port from the iPhone version. There are weird texture errors at the bottom of the screen since I have a taller screen than iPhones and there's other texturing issues where I can see texture edges in common graphics. It also runs oddly slow. I write my own games on my own phone with more sprites and more complex physics and they run better. Also, the music instrumentation sounds off -- again, as if the score was shoe-horned into a different synthesizer.  I expected a far better port for a game that's proven to sell. Instead what I got was a cheap money grab -- my hats off to them, they got my money.
